column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Sunny and 74 Light winds and calm waters. Weeds starting to get thicker every year.

column1: Weeds seem to have gotten worse ever since the cranberry bogs went in on the South side of the lake. Also noticeable difference since the potato fields started back in operation.

column2: Water level has gone down a few feet- ever since the potato fields started irrigating. Also notice a lot more weeds since the potato fields and cranberry bogs went in.
Water is open around the gage for 50 feet
Calm and 51 degrees. Loons on the lake and no wind
Sunny and 72 degrees. Lots of boat traffic. Weeds are starting to hit the surface.
Weeds are staring to take over the lake like back in 1987. Pretty sure it?s all the fertilizer and chemicals from the potato and cranberry bogs located west of the lake. Sad that nothing can be done.
Weeds getting Thick. Fishing has dropped dramatically
